'''Waterhen Lake''' is a lake in [[Manitoba]], [[Canada]], located about 300 km north of the provincial capital of [[Winnipeg]], between [[Lake Winnipeg]] and [[Lake Winnipegosis]].<ref>{{CGNDB|id=GBDHS|name=Waterhen Lake}}</ref> 

From Long Island Bay at the southeast end of Lake Winnipegosis the West Waterhen and Little Waterhen rivers flow north about 16 km (10 miles) into Waterhen Lake then the [[Waterhen River (Manitoba)|Waterhen River]] flows south 22 km (13.5 miles) into the northern end of [[Lake Manitoba]].<ref name="Distance Calculator">{{cite web| url=http://www.daftlogic.com/projects-google-maps-distance-calculator.htm|title=Google Maps Distance Calculator| accessdate=2014-12-22}}</ref>

[[Waterhen Indian Reserve No. 45]], aka "Waterhen", which is the reserve community of the [[Skownan First Nation]], is located on its south shore.<ref>[http://pse5-esd5.ainc-inac.gc.ca/FNP/Main/Search/RVDetail.aspx?RESERVE_NUMBER=06395&lang=eng Indian and Northern Affairs Canada Reserve/Settlement/Village Detail]</ref>

